    • Method Detail

      • getChildren

        protected abstract java.util.Collection<N> getChildren(N node)
        Returns a list of child nodes for the specified node. This method is called by the walker only if the visitor returned the CONTINUE action. The walker will be paused if it returns null. To continue user should call the setChildren(java.util.Collection<? extends N>) method.
        Parameters:
        node - a node in a tree structure
        Returns:
        children for the specified node or null if children will be set later
